The user's typing speed increased from 9 words per minute to 12 words per minute over a period of 5 minutes, which would be an increase of approximately 37.5%. This is calculated as follows:

Increase = (New Rate - Old Rate) / Old Rate * 100%
          = ((12 WPM - 9 WPM)/9 WPM)*100%
          = 37.5%

So, the user's typing speed increased by approximately 37.5%.
